</newversion></questtextxml></cc1gt28f><cc1gt001><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Talk to Gladys
desc=You don't look like a fool explorer, who is obsessed with the magic stones in Exeter Island. The magic stones are a precious treasure which makes a magic spell stronger, but it is also a wicked jewel which fascinates people, making them abandon their hometown. Many people expect wealth from an exploration for the magic stone, but they actually end up losing more valuable things, such as friendship or their lifes.
Please don't get blinded by selfishness and find something that you are truely looking for.

 Anyways, I heard that Gladys from the trading market was looking for someone. That could be you. If you go east of the ferry station, you will see the shipbuilding yard. The trading market is located north of the shipbuilding yard.

Go to the shipbuilding yard and talk to Gladys.
runDlg=Gladys is still a smart kid as usual, but she became a lightheaded person. Just like every other young people. They don't care about inheritance from the ancestors of Exeter. Being fascinated by the Magistri, they are only interested in collecting goods.
finishDlg=Hello. I heard a lot about you from Lennon of the trading market in Castle Hall. Time is running. Let's talk about the subject.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Talk to Gladys
