runDlg=Kevin thinks it is his fault when he saw ships with damaged masts and wrecked. I know he is a hard worker, but he thinks too much.
finishDlg=I am sorry. We ran out of the materials so I can't fix the ship. Oh, can you show me that box? Oh my... These are the materials I ordered. I thought I would never find them. Thank you very much. Now I can fix ships.
</newversion></questtextxml></cc1gt003><cc1gt004><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hunt Cursed Werwolf
desc=Oh my, here is another follower who wants to hear about the great Tyler's adventure. A story about how I protected General Hawker by fighting the dark monsters in the Tulach Dungeon, how I dealt with the scary dark captain, and how I chased the giant monster, Crewbarian alone on the ocean. There is never enough time for my stories.

Glostern is threatened by the monster.
 Those monsters attack people who collect the magic stones. Such a headache.

Go hunt Cursed Werwolf and report it to Elsy, the weapon trader. If you succeed, I will tell you the rest of my great stories of adventures.
startDlg=Ouch... My scars are stinging. Will it rain?
runDlg=Be careful when you catch Cursed Werwolf. Their skin is as hard as a rock, so your weapon could be damaged. Anyways, go see Elsy.
finishDlg=You are the one Tyler has talked about. It is amazing that you hunt that amount of Cursed Werwolf. I asked Tyler to do it, but now I know why he picked you for his job. Like the teacher, like the student. Because of your great work, now it's easier and safer to dig out the magic stones.  
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunt Cursed Werwolf
