desc=Marigold said that? Did I say something like that? Not good... Telling the task is a piece of cake but does not mean I would do it, doesn't it?

Anyway, it is manlike to take care of pretty womans.

Almost the whole place in Exeter Island is explored by people. Gloshire is the only place which remains intact. There is a mysterious power in that area. My blood could feel it. Investigating old things from the past... what could it be?

Right, there are monsters, we call them shrine spearman. They are some kind of moving stone, wandering around the abandoned grave or Merfolk ruins in the north. No one knows who made them and why they can move around.

Go and destroy the statues and collect some interesting pieces from them. Bring these pieces to Marigold. The pieces might be special like stone printed with magical characters or rune pictures. Please bring those runes to Marigold. I know you can do it. 
startDlg=Echew... This pain... I shouldn't had kicked the blanket yesterday.
runDlg=Did you collect all the runes? Hurry up! Don't make the woman wait so long. You are not going to upset her, are you?
finishDlg=Runes from the spearman in the temple? You found them at your investigation? How interesting! I've never seen anything like that before. Is it ok to leave them in the store? There won't be any curse from it like turning beer into vinegar?
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Collect the Spearman Shrine Rune in the dungeon
