desc=Merfolk heritage? I thought there are only monsters living in Gloshire.

Right, I think I heard the reason: There are many magic stones in Gloshire due to some kind of heritage of the past.

However, because I am not interested in the magic stones, I never paid attention to those stories. It must be really boring to dig into ground all the time. I wouldn't mind if I was born as a mole.

Take these runes to Lennon, the trading manager. He is also investigating Tulach Dungeon under General Renfield's order. According to Tyler, he did Lennon a big favor before. Lennon will be happy to see you if Tyler sent you.
runDlg=History about Gloshire? I told you I am not interested in those kind of stuff. You can hear that from people like Gregory, the dock manager. Well, he would not be very happy to see you because the elder people in Glostern do not like people who look for treasures or magic stones.
finishDlg=It's been a long time. The Shrine Spearmens' Runes of Gloshire heritage? How interesting. It will be a good comparison to Tulach Dungeon for my investigation. However, I've never heard of the name Tyler. Marigold mistook me for someone else.
