desc=I asked the Noble Masquer Lord Ian to investigate those pieces. According to Lord Ian, there is some kind of magic power spread over those Pottery Pieces and Stone Pieces. 

However, these aren't natural magic stones. It is a part of the ordinary heritage. But something affected it, giving it magic power.

We have to find out from which area of the Gloshire heritage the pieces did come from. Harbor manager Gregory, is the person who knows the most about Gloshire. He could probably tell you their origin. Show him these pieces.  
runDlg=Thank you for helping Elsy. Don't get confused. I still don't like explorers. If they do not appreciate their own places, they won't care about other places either. However, you did my friend a favor, who is really worried about Glostern. I just thank you for this. Don't just stand there. Go to the ferry station.
finishDlg=Are you sailing out? Wait a minute. I am recording the report. Maybe it is from age, that I easily forget everything if I don't write it down. Huh? What is that box for?
