desc=The pieces from Blue Gangster? This is amazing. These pieces look like they came from some kind of building.
Look at the work on every piece. The patterns of the works are all the same. I think I saw something like that...

Right! These are pieces from the Merfolk Altar. According to the myth, Merfolk, the tribe of the sea, made the Gloshire heritage. When I was young, I explored Gloshire myself out of curiosity. And I found the Merfolk Altar. But nobody was there. Although it was abandoned, it was still beautiful. And there was radiating some strange power. I can't believe that beautiful altar has been threatened. ...

Go to Gloshire and see how much of the Merfolk Altar is damaged. I hope the damage is not too heavy.
runDlg=When I was young, the elders said that the Merfolk made the heritage of Gloshire. Do you wanna know how they accessed the ground inside of Exeter Island from the sea? According to legend, they used the Seahorse Stone to make the sea water flow into Gloshire. That's the reason, why we have a water path in Gloshire. How about the Merfolk Altar? Is it still ok?
finishDlg=...You are a greater man than I thought. Thank you. The breakage extent is not as serious as I thought. Because of you, the precious Merfolk Altar won't be damaged anymore. That's good.  
 Thank you for doing me that huge favor. I wish people would know that a great adventurer like you exists.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Discover Merfolk Altar
