 Thank you for doing me a huge favor. I wish people will know that a great adventurer like you exists.
</newversion></questtextxml></cc1gt016><cc1gt017><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Hunt Vismann
desc=Nowadays, sailing people think Merfolk are only violent monsters. However, this is wrong.

They aquired a great wisdom we can't even imagine. The heritage of Gloshire and the Vismann prove their wisdom. Vismanns which stroll up and down the Daigon Hill in Gloshire are the creation of Merfolk. They were the guard for the heritage when Merfolk lived in Gloshire. They were a wise existence which only attacked those who tried to harm the heritage and showed mercy to those who were weaker than them. However, now they turned into different cruel and violent monsters. On top of attacking the explorer of Gloshire, they plan to assault Glostern. We need to stop that!

Go to Daigon Hill of Gloshire and get rid of the Vismann.
runDlg=Did you get them? I don't know how they turned like that. Perhaps, it is because the water on the water path dried and the land changed, looking like this. It's just my opinion.
finishDlg=Thank you. Because of you, people in Glostern will have a peaceful life.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunt Vismann
