</newversion></questtextxml></cc1gt017><cc1gt018><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Report to Lady Avery
desc=Long time ago, Merfolk were called the guardians. They directed and protected many sea creatures. Although they possessed great power, they showed mercy to weak creatures. There was a story that a ship, attacked by sea monsters, was saved by Merfolk.

You don't believe me? But it is true.
Then why did they turn out so monsterous now?

Lady Avery, the Lord of Glostern would probably know why the Merfolk abandoned Gloshire and returned to the sea. People who know this kind of stuff very well would obviously be noble people on Exeter Island.

Go to Lady Avery, talk to her about what has happened so far in Gloshire and tell her my opinion. 
runDlg=I think Gloshire looks like this now because Merfolk has turned their back on humans, but it is just my opinion. I don't know the real reason. If we could find out the reason, people can have a good relationship with Merfolk once again.
finishDlg=I am the Lord of this Island, Avery. Looks like you have something to tell me. Relax and go on.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Report to Lady Avery
