desc=The relation between Merfolk and Gloshire heritage&#x2026;
Did you say Gregory? He is a very sharp person.

It is right, that Merfolk made Gloshire heritage. According to records preserved in the document safe in the kingdom, the Merfolk temple's original name was literally Golden Wave Temple. The Merfolk worshiped this temple. There were many Seahorse Stones, the magic stones inside the temple. At the beginning, people lived happily together with Merfolks. However, as Weremoles broke in for stealing the treasures, the peace was broken. As you know, Weremoles do not know how to give up. The Merfolk could not stand the Weremoles' attack and destruction any longer, so they returned to the sea with the help of the Seahorse Stones.

It is an old story. It happened before the 30-year-old War occured when my royal family was about to settle in Exeter Island. Since then, Merfolk consider every creatures on land as enemies. It is really sad.
runDlg=Unfortunately, there is no record about the reason the Merfolk came to live on land in the first place. Maybe, we will get more information if we look at the records of other islands.
finishDlg=In fact, I heard your name by the villagers. I was impressed that you are helping people who aren't even related to you. We, people in Glostern will never forget about you. I hope the passion in your good heart will last forever.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Talk to Lady Avery
