desc=A-ha! So Willy sent you, huh? What a relief. We have been receiving many newcomer adventurers, but since they were not that skilled it wasn't really working out! I've been concerned about Cotton Mushrooms lately. At first, Cotton Mushrooms were just simple mushrooms. Because of their good quality, smell and taste, people from other islands would come to pick them.

However, recently a very skinny pale figure with a book in his arms went into the Fox Den and everything changed ever since. Dark force flowed out of the Fox Den and suddenly the monsters in Weedridge began to go wild! Well... Honestly, adventurers such as myself can't really tell but since the noblemen of this city say that they can feel the dark force, it might be true.

But what's more important, the Cotton Mushrooms were brought to life and began to move around. Not knowing this, some girls who went to pick the mushrooms were attacked by them. Now we can't have Roxbury's special recipe, Cotton Mushroom stew no more. Some very few brave men have pursued the Mushrooms but now Tiny Goldbugs are attacking people, too.

So, could you go catch me some of those Cotton Mushrooms? I will pay you enough. I would like to go myself but as you know I'm too busy recruiting newcomer adventurers. What do you say?
startDlg=.
runDlg=Some tough Mushrooms, huh? Goldbugs flying all around... Won't be that easy. Good luck!
finishDlg=Wow! You're awesome! You've done something even experienced adventurers find difficult to do. You smell like the Mushrooms after dealing with them. It's good to smell them again. Well done. Here's the reward I've promised you before.
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Hunt Cotton Mushroom
