</newversion></questtextxml></ac2gt016><ac2gt017><questtextxml><oldversion> Mission1=Talk to Geronimo
desc=Now Tulach Temple is very dangerous, but many years ago, Draug only scared people away from the temple, not agressively dominated people.

However, eight years ago before I became the general, one Constable took his troop to Tulach Temple in order to get rid of the Draugs. They left the youngest as messenger outside and bravely went into the temple.
However, the rest of the soldiers never came back. When the messenger heard the loud screams after a while, he ran away.

After pulling himself together, he waited for the troop outside the temple, but he could never see them again. In mourning over the death of the soldiers, he came back to Castle Hall and told the Constable about it. Then the Constable took another troop for search. However, the troop could not win over the Draug and the other monsters, which agressively attacked the troop and eventually backed out.

The messenger was so disappointed, he quit being a soldier, looking for another job. That guy is Geronimo, the owner of the weapon shop. The reason I am telling you this story is that I think you are the man who could remove his burden of sadness.

Now, go and visit Geronimo and tell him, that I told you the story, and help him out.  
runDlg=Now, it's time for Genonimo to get out of the nightmare. He used to be a brave soldier.
finishDlg=What's up? If you come to the weapon store, please hurry up picking up your weapon. 
</oldversion><newversion> Mission1=Talk to Geronimo
