desc=After you got rid of little Rose, the power of vampire noble who followed her will, was severely weakened.
But that doesn't mean they lost their power completely. Maybe little Rose was used for their solidarity. But exactly it was little Baron she followed.

I trusted him with the experiments but couldn't get out of responsibility and guiltiness. Meanwhile I did my best for the sealing of underground laboratory, but as you know, the seal was removed. I think the force of darkness became stronger in the Underground Laboratory. We have to find out what Little Baron did in the meantime.

There is something I am concerned about. As we researched the extracting of magic essence, we spent much money for jewelry consumption. That money was supported secretly by Lord Avery through the Magistri, they wanted to seize the town.

Even if Lord Avery and I did that job, we had a justification. But the criticism from Divine Association, they follow principle, was fatal. Without any choice, we decided to seal the underground, but the Magistri protested strongly.

Even Gladis of the Magistri stood in my way. At that time little Baron brought a group of experiment targets. We got frightened out of our senses for their great destructive power, but at the end of complications we could arrange guardians for the sealing. They were also experiment targets.

Anyway, I expect a great conspiracy between little Baron, trying to overcome the limit of experiments and the Magistri's support to keep the experiments.

Little Baron must be related to that conspiracy, so get rid of him and find a clue.
runDlg=If we catch little Baron we could go close to the center of underground laboratory.
finishDlg=Maegner? Did you find the clue of him? It's time that Magistri has to step forward anyhow.
